        "requiresAdditionalCondition": false,
        "treatmentContext": "initial-treatment"
      },
      "overallDuration": "26 weeks",
      "followUpDuration": "6 weeks",
      "safetySummary": "Gastrointestinal disorders occurred in 41%-63% across cagrilintide doses versus 32% with placebo; nausea was the most frequent event. Serious adverse events occurred in 2-7% of cagrilintide arms vs. 4% (liraglutide) and 3% (placebo); nausea (20-47% vs. 39% liraglutide, 18% placebo) and vomiting (5-9% vs. 20% liraglutide, 3% placebo) increased with cagrilintide dose. Anti-cagrilintide antibodies occurred in 46-73% of participants by week 26, increasing with dose; per-arm figures were not given in the accessible main text (only a range). No deaths occurred.",
